Pre-Game Insights: Czech Republic must win to replicate their run to the quarter-finals of the last European Championship.
Patrick Schick may be missing through injury, and Prague-based pair Jan Kuchta and Mojmir Chytil could be called upon to deputise.
Adam Hlozek is likely to come under consideration.
Hasek introduced Chytil, Antonin Barak and Ondrej Lingr from the bench at the weekend, but at least two of the three may start at Volksparkstadion.
Viktoria Plzen midfielder Pavel Sulc was a surprise starter against Portugal, so Hasek will also consider his claim.
The established back three of Tomas Holes, Ladislav Krejci and Robin Hranac is unlikely to change.
Captain Tomas Soucek and his West Ham United teammate Vladimir Coufal are certainly assured of their places.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Czech Republic won the match 1-2 against Turkey.
Key players: Soucek (66'), Barak (11'), Schick (34'), Jaros (84'), Cerv (85'), Krejci (90+1'), Soucek (90+8') for Czech Republic.
